{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":880,"text":"So, this is a story"},{"time":2904,"text":"about how we know what we know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":5690,"text":"It's a story about this woman,"},{"time":8611,"text":"Natalia Rybczynski."},{"time":10912,"text":"She's a paleobiologist,"},{"time":12984,"text":"which means she specializes\nin digging up really old dead stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":16837,"text":"(Audio) Natalia Rybczynski: Yeah,\nI had someone call me \"Dr. Dead Things.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":20363,"text":"Latif Nasser: And I think\nshe's particularly interesting"},{"time":23016,"text":"because of where she digs that stuff up,"},{"time":24954,"text":"way above the Arctic Circle\nin the remote Canadian tundra."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29901,"text":"Now, one summer day in 2006,"},{"time":32980,"text":"she was at a dig site called\nthe Fyles Leaf Bed,"},{"time":36195,"text":"which is less than 10 degrees latitude\naway from the magnetic north pole."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40797,"text":"(Audio) NR: Really, it's not\ngoing to sound very exciting,"},{"time":43548,"text":"because it was a day of walking\nwith your backpack and your GPS"},{"time":47602,"text":"and notebook and just picking up\nanything that might be a fossil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51704,"text":"LN: And at some point,\nshe noticed something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54403,"text":"(Audio) NR: Rusty, kind of rust-colored,"},{"time":56594,"text":"about the size of the palm of my hand."},{"time":58553,"text":"It was just lying on the surface."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60871,"text":"LN: And at first she thought\nit was just a splinter of wood,"},{"time":64347,"text":"because that's the sort of thing\npeople had found"},{"time":66664,"text":"at the Fyles Leaf Bed before --\nprehistoric plant parts."},{"time":70107,"text":"But that night, back at camp ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72940,"text":"(Audio) NR: ... I get out the hand lens,"},{"time":74893,"text":"I'm looking a little bit\nmore closely and realizing"},{"time":77314,"text":"it doesn't quite look\nlike this has tree rings."},{"time":79742,"text":"Maybe it's a preservation thing,"},{"time":81330,"text":"but it looks really like ..."},{"time":83628,"text":"bone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84853,"text":"LN: Huh. So over the next four years,"},{"time":87766,"text":"she went to that spot over and over,"},{"time":90724,"text":"and eventually collected 30 fragments\nof that exact same bone,"},{"time":96284,"text":"most of them really tiny."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98522,"text":"(Audio) NR: It's not a whole lot.\nIt fits in a small Ziploc bag."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102982,"text":"LN: And she tried to piece them\ntogether like a jigsaw puzzle."},{"time":106941,"text":"But it was challenging."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108410,"text":"(Audio) NR: It's broken up\ninto so many little tiny pieces,"},{"time":111254,"text":"I'm trying to use sand and putty,\nand it's not looking good."},{"time":115536,"text":"So finally, we used a 3D surface scanner."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120727,"text":"LN: Ooh!\nNR: Yeah, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":122340,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":123804,"text":"LN: It turns out it was way easier\nto do it virtually."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126571,"text":"(Audio) NR: It's kind of magical\nwhen it all fits together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129365,"text":"LN: How certain were you\nthat you had it right,"},{"time":131588,"text":"that you had put it together\nin the right way?"},{"time":133757,"text":"Was there a potential that you'd\nput it together a different way"},{"time":136795,"text":"and have, like, a parakeet or something?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":138761,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":140150,"text":"(Audio) NR: (Laughs) Um, no.\nNo, we got this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144242,"text":"LN: What she had, she discovered,\nwas a tibia, a leg bone,"},{"time":148107,"text":"and specifically, one that belonged\nto a cloven-hoofed mammal,"},{"time":152131,"text":"so something like a cow or a sheep."},{"time":155004,"text":"But it couldn't have been either of those."},{"time":157488,"text":"It was just too big."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159822,"text":"(Audio) NR: The size of this thing,\nit was huge. It's a really big animal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163910,"text":"LN: So what animal could it be?"},{"time":167291,"text":"Having hit a wall, she showed\none of the fragments"},{"time":169895,"text":"to some colleagues of hers in Colorado,"},{"time":172491,"text":"and they had an idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174244,"text":"(Audio) NR: We took a saw,\nand we nicked just the edge of it,"},{"time":179315,"text":"and there was this really interesting\nsmell that comes from it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186521,"text":"LN: It smelled kind of like singed flesh."},{"time":189308,"text":"It was a smell that Natalia recognized"},{"time":191965,"text":"from cutting up skulls\nin her gross anatomy lab:"},{"time":195932,"text":"collagen."},{"time":197120,"text":"Collagen is what gives\nstructure to our bones."},{"time":199801,"text":"And usually, after so many years,"},{"time":201983,"text":"it breaks down."},{"time":203158,"text":"But in this case, the Arctic had acted\nlike a natural freezer and preserved it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208190,"text":"Then a year or two later,\nNatalia was at a conference in Bristol,"},{"time":211837,"text":"and she saw that a colleague\nof hers named Mike Buckley"},{"time":215055,"text":"was demoing this new process\nthat he called \"collagen fingerprinting.\""},{"time":221284,"text":"It turns out that different species\nhave slightly different structures"},{"time":224951,"text":"of collagen,"},{"time":226127,"text":"so if you get a collagen profile\nof an unknown bone,"},{"time":228967,"text":"you can compare it\nto those of known species,"},{"time":231185,"text":"and, who knows, maybe you get a match."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234546,"text":"So she shipped him one of the fragments,"},{"time":237849,"text":"FedEx."}]},{"cues":[{"time":239167,"text":"(Audio) NR: Yeah, you want to track it.\nIt's kind of important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243001,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":244278,"text":"LN: And he processed it,"},{"time":245493,"text":"and compared it to 37 known\nand modern-day mammal species."},{"time":250674,"text":"And he found a match."},{"time":252824,"text":"It turns out that\nthe 3.5 million-year-old bone"},{"time":257460,"text":"that Natalia had dug\nout of the High Arctic"},{"time":261729,"text":"belonged to ..."},{"time":264031,"text":"a camel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265372,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":267127,"text":"(Audio) NR: And I'm thinking, what?\nThat's amazing -- if it's true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271449,"text":"LN: So they tested\na bunch of the fragments,"},{"time":273525,"text":"and they got the same result for each one."},{"time":276197,"text":"However, based on the size\nof the bone that they found,"},{"time":281641,"text":"it meant that this camel was 30 percent\nlarger than modern-day camels."},{"time":288028,"text":"So this camel would have been\nabout nine feet tall,"},{"time":291242,"text":"weighed around a ton."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292464,"text":"(Audience reacts)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":293539,"text":"Yeah."},{"time":294612,"text":"Natalia had found a Giant Arctic camel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298129,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":302396,"text":"Now, when you hear the word \"camel,\""},{"time":304738,"text":"what may come to mind is one of these,"},{"time":309507,"text":"the Bactrian camel\nof East and Central Asia."},{"time":312895,"text":"But chances are the postcard image\nyou have in your brain"},{"time":316404,"text":"is one of these, the dromedary,"},{"time":319983,"text":"quintessential desert creature --"},{"time":322435,"text":"hangs out in sandy, hot places\nlike the Middle East and the Sahara,"},{"time":326778,"text":"has a big old hump on its back"},{"time":328282,"text":"for storing water\nfor those long desert treks,"},{"time":330823,"text":"has big, broad feet to help it\ntromp over sand dunes."},{"time":334918,"text":"So how on earth would one of these guys\nend up in the High Arctic?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":341719,"text":"Well, scientists have known\nfor a long time, turns out,"},{"time":344530,"text":"even before Natalia's discovery,"},{"time":347116,"text":"that camels are actually\noriginally American."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352758,"text":"(Music: The Star-Spangled Banner)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":358482,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":359965,"text":"They started here."},{"time":361520,"text":"For nearly 40 of the 45 million years\nthat camels have been around,"},{"time":366378,"text":"you could only find them in North America,"},{"time":369561,"text":"around 20 different species, maybe more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":372838,"text":"(Audio) LN: If I put them all in a lineup,\nwould they look different?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":376107,"text":"NR: Yeah, you're going to have\ndifferent body sizes."},{"time":378566,"text":"You'll have some with really long necks,"},{"time":380502,"text":"so they're actually\nfunctionally like giraffes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":383345,"text":"LN: Some had snouts, like crocodiles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386441,"text":"(Audio) NR: The really primitive,\nearly ones would have been really small,"},{"time":390049,"text":"almost like rabbits."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392576,"text":"LN: What? Rabbit-sized camels?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":395447,"text":"(Audio) NR: The earliest ones."},{"time":396908,"text":"So those ones you probably\nwould not recognize."}]},{"cues":[{"time":399167,"text":"LN: Oh my God, I want a pet rabbit-camel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401381,"text":"(Audio) NR: I know,\nwouldn't that be great?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":403449,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":404645,"text":"LN: And then about three\nto seven million years ago,"},{"time":407328,"text":"one branch of camels\nwent down to South America,"},{"time":410160,"text":"where they became llamas and alpacas,"},{"time":413138,"text":"and another branch crossed over\nthe Bering Land Bridge"},{"time":416084,"text":"into Asia and Africa."},{"time":417544,"text":"And then around the end\nof the last ice age,"},{"time":419989,"text":"North American camels went extinct."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423893,"text":"So, scientists knew all of that already,"},{"time":426337,"text":"but it still doesn't fully explain\nhow Natalia found one so far north."},{"time":432437,"text":"Like, this is, temperature-wise,\nthe polar opposite of the Sahara."},{"time":437135,"text":"Now to be fair,"},{"time":439660,"text":"three and a half million years ago,"},{"time":441367,"text":"it was on average 22 degrees Celsius\nwarmer than it is now."},{"time":445490,"text":"So it would have been boreal forest,"},{"time":448449,"text":"so more like the Yukon or Siberia today."},{"time":452853,"text":"But still, like, they would have\nsix-month-long winters"},{"time":456583,"text":"where the ponds would freeze over."},{"time":458830,"text":"You'd have blizzards."},{"time":460322,"text":"You'd have 24 hours a day\nof straight darkness."},{"time":463957,"text":"Like, how ... How?"},{"time":466962,"text":"How is it that one of these\nSaharan superstars"},{"time":471144,"text":"could ever have survived\nthose arctic conditions?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":474399,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":477399,"text":"Natalia and her colleagues\nthink they have an answer."},{"time":481632,"text":"And it's kind of brilliant."},{"time":484700,"text":"What if the very features that we imagine\nmake the camel so well-suited"},{"time":491257,"text":"to places like the Sahara,"},{"time":493249,"text":"actually evolved to help it\nget through the winter?"},{"time":497448,"text":"What if those broad feet were meant\nto tromp not over sand,"},{"time":502169,"text":"but over snow, like a pair of snowshoes?"},{"time":505792,"text":"What if that hump --\nwhich, huge news to me,"},{"time":508617,"text":"does not contain water, it contains fat --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":511015,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":512618,"text":"was there to help the camel\nget through that six-month-long winter,"},{"time":516243,"text":"when food was scarce?"},{"time":517944,"text":"And then, only later, long after\nit crossed over the land bridge"},{"time":521681,"text":"did it retrofit those winter features\nfor a hot desert environment?"},{"time":526123,"text":"Like, for instance, the hump\nmay be helpful to camels in hotter climes"},{"time":530221,"text":"because having all your fat in one place,"},{"time":532717,"text":"like a, you know, fat backpack,"},{"time":535482,"text":"means that you don't have\nto have that insulation"},{"time":538034,"text":"all over the rest of your body."},{"time":539817,"text":"So it helps heat dissipate easier."},{"time":542555,"text":"It's this crazy idea,"},{"time":545420,"text":"that what seems like proof of the camel's\nquintessential desert nature"},{"time":550991,"text":"could actually be proof\nof its High Arctic past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":555832,"text":"Now, I'm not the first person\nto tell this story."},{"time":559566,"text":"Others have told it as a way\nto marvel at evolutionary biology"},{"time":564540,"text":"or as a keyhole into the future\nof climate change."},{"time":568855,"text":"But I love it for a totally\ndifferent reason."},{"time":571751,"text":"For me, it's a story about us,"},{"time":574537,"text":"about how we see the world"},{"time":576529,"text":"and about how that changes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579658,"text":"So I was trained as a historian."},{"time":583054,"text":"And I've learned that, actually,\na lot of scientists are historians, too."},{"time":587331,"text":"They make sense of the past."},{"time":588904,"text":"They tell the history of our universe,\nof our planet, of life on this planet."},{"time":594741,"text":"And as a historian,"},{"time":596242,"text":"you start with an idea in your mind\nof how the story goes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":601196,"text":"(Audio) NR: We make up stories\nand we stick with it,"},{"time":603705,"text":"like the camel in the desert, right?"},{"time":605451,"text":"That's a great story!\nIt's totally adapted for that."},{"time":607921,"text":"Clearly, it always lived there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":610174,"text":"LN: But at any moment, you could\nuncover some tiny bit of evidence."},{"time":614500,"text":"You could learn some tiny thing"},{"time":616723,"text":"that forces you to reframe\neverything you thought you knew."},{"time":620706,"text":"Like, in this case, this one scientist\nfinds this one shard"},{"time":624508,"text":"of what she thought was wood,"},{"time":626279,"text":"and because of that, science has a totally\nnew and totally counterintuitive theory"},{"time":631341,"text":"about why this absurd\nDr. Seuss-looking creature"},{"time":634980,"text":"looks the way it does."},{"time":636536,"text":"And for me, it completely upended\nthe way I think of the camel."},{"time":641964,"text":"It went from being\nthis ridiculously niche creature"},{"time":646370,"text":"suited only to this\none specific environment,"},{"time":648743,"text":"to being this world traveler\nthat just happens to be in the Sahara,"},{"time":654055,"text":"and could end up virtually anywhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":657880,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":674396,"text":"This is Azuri."},{"time":676589,"text":"Azuri, hi, how are you doing?"},{"time":679493,"text":"OK, here, I've got\none of these for you here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":682065,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":684135,"text":"So Azuri is on a break\nfrom her regular gig"},{"time":688342,"text":"at the Radio City Music Hall."}]},{"cues":[{"time":690589,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":692762,"text":"That's not even a joke."},{"time":694717,"text":"Anyway --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":696478,"text":"But really, Azuri is here\nas a living reminder"},{"time":700859,"text":"that the story of our world\nis a dynamic one."},{"time":705130,"text":"It requires our willingness\nto readjust, to reimagine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":709861,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":714162,"text":"Right, Azuri?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":715637,"text":"And, really, that we're all\njust one shard of bone away"},{"time":722077,"text":"from seeing the world anew."}]},{"cues":[{"time":724926,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":726110,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}